It is good if your usage is light or if you do not go into crowded environments. The glass and case are quite delicate and get scratched very easily. This watch also looks very simple and it can be a bit difficult to see the time in a hurry as there are no numbers on it. It does not look very exciting but if you are looking for a simple watch then it might be good. The mostly black colour makes dust particles visible and anyone can see if your watch is dirty. You can find a better watch at this price which has a metal case and strong glass because even if it isn't from a "good" company it will still last long and maintain its shine throughout the usage.

In straight words, It's good in a budget but compared to options like MI band it's thrash the screen is slower, Smaller and Less responsive than all other options (That I know of) and the battery sucks only lasts about 1.5 to 2 days if brigntness is normal and all PAI options are turned off.Otherwise build quality is good and Accuracy is okayish.

I had the miband 4 but then came here considering data privacy. Reflex is a let down in all aspects.It has very big display but it is mostly the bezel feeling that is seen and LCD makes it disappointing.Accuracy : Is goodBattery life : let down. With all notifications (basic calls) Max we get is 3-4 days. With notifications enabled it doesn't cross 3 days(plan to recharge twice in a week). Charging is easy here.App: disappointed with the fact that it needs internet to update watch data to app. I understand with respect to the global or local ranking but when watch is connected via bluetooth, it should sync without internet as well which is not the case. So it becomes a task to manually sync each day. It was not the case with MI band. App doesn't give you ability to track like a graph instead it shows the intensity on daily basis but I do not get the bar graph or the pie chart of the previous week steps.Go for it but get it at least possible price. And it still is made in china(PRC) as per the brand although the box states made in India. Only good part is, the data of self will not be stored outside country which I a big possitive.

I went for this band as I didn't want to buy Mi band 5(I already own Mi band 4). Short answer is I dont want to continue using it and there is no option to return, you can only replace which is bad.What I like :I love its design, its pretty stylish. I think it looks much better than Mi or honor bands. It tracks your activities automatically but its very slow to recognise the same. It has all the basic tracking activities and little more as well.What I don't like :Touch response is not great. Even my mi 4 has better response than this.Very limited band face like literally around 10 or something.The reflex world app is pretty basic.Battery has gone down to 53% already within 3 days without bluetooth being connected to device.Issues I faced (still facing) :I was able to complete initial setup using app but then after that the app doesn't start, it just force closes automatically. I tried reinstalling, restarting, providing manual permissions.I dropped an email to titan customer care and then after 2 3 hours I called them explaining my issue and then they asked me to send a video showing the issue and a ticket was created. In short its almost waste of time and experience. I have oneplus 7 and running Android 11 and they said it has nothing to do with the same.That being said i was able to setup with using my wife phone (redmi note7 pro). 2 days have past since then and I haven't got any response from customer care.My experience is spoilt and I have ordered Samsung fit2 and will give this to my dad or mom or wife :).

There is no way you can set your own custom timer and keep it as a tile in the timer app. (Available in cheaper watches)2. User interface is pretty dry, not much use of colors and they didn't even try to make it much user friendly. I have to pull the app drawer and select music everytime I want to change the Music via my the watch.3. The auto wake feature in the watch is the weakest I have seen in any smart watch, cheaper watches than this are much faster and responsive than this.4. The app is ridiculous too, alot of important features are either missing or hidden and you have to dig them everytime when you want to use them. The app doesn't support dark mode which is like a pretty basic thing at this point.Pros:1. The tracking accuracy is on spot. Didn't see any lag or irregularities in the data it showed.2. The bigger screen does come in handy and is easier to maneuver through.3. Connects to Bluetooth of the phone faster than most other watches.Conclusion:The hardware of the watch is pretty solid, but there is a massive miss in the software department, which needs a big revamp.

The watch was expected. Personally I preferred this watch over competition was simply because it was imported by Titan. Which I expected to maintain a minimum quality & it did not disappoint. Accuracy of the sensors are difficult for me to judge as I do not have medical equipments to compare. Also, if I go by the reviews - even the most expensive smart watches are not completely accurate.However, I have noted a strange 'bug' - the step count on the Fastrack app does not match with the step count of Google Fit App. Since My Google Fit app is connected with the watch, they are supposed to be identical IMHO. Another isssue is that if you take a nap during the day time - it is not reflected in 'Sleep', wonder why!Final question to Amazon: I believe I purchased the black version (not 100% sure) but the order does not mention the color. Why ? I am saying this because I got the blue colored case with a black dial. If there are multiple colors available, why color is not mentioned on the order ?

1. 'lift to view' is really slow and sometimes the watch does not wake up.2. Time format / mode: the watch does not have 12Hr / 24Hr format/mode time selection option. I could not find it anywhere! I think this is a small but important feature which could have been provided.3. I did not get any strap loop to hold the extended portion of strap with the wrapped portion of strap. These two numbers of loops were missing in the box!All other features and battery backup is good. Hope manufacturer will provide some software update to enable 12/24 Hr Time mode/format.About Time Format: On 18-10-2022, I just found that since the watch is synchronized with your mobile, the time format of watch is governed by the time format of your mobile. If you change the time format of your mobile, the time format of your watch will also change.

I have ordered two units of the same watch one for me (red) and one for my brother in law (blue).The red colour watch is so far is working good and blue watch battery got drained out quickly and not charging back. The red colour watch battery got charged and it's giving around two days runtime. I have raised a replacement for blue but seller didn't have the replacement so Amazon promised to refund the money (thanks Amazon).There are couple of exceptions here and the main one is it's only 1M water resistant not even 5M which almost all watches provide. There is no IP67 or IP68 reading for dust and water resistant which now a days most of the smartwatches provide, even the Rs. 1500/- OnePlus band provides.The blood pressure rating is not accurate when compared to a medical device but it will give an idea how much is the difference (around 10 to 20 reading less). The SPO2 and heart rate reading are accurate.With the price we are paying and issues i am facing giving 3 stars only.

The packaging used by Amazon was really good.Coming to the packaging of the watch itself, wow, the unboxing experience was really clean.And coming to the sensors, it has Heart rate and SpO2, BLOOD PRESSURE sensors etc.1. The Heart rate sensor works fines with a margin of error of 2-3 beats per min.2. The SpO2 sensor is not a gimmick, it works fine but not 100% accurate, it was of by nearly 2% every time3. BLOOD PRESSURE sensor work fine with a margin of error 5-10** All the sensors do no work if the watch is not on your hand**So ALL are just not for namesake and are functional.**It doesn't have GPS built-in the only CON at this price.**The display is pretty good and gets adequately bright.Coming to the battery charging time, it takes around 1.5hrs for 30-100%.The battery only lasts for 3 days, when HR set for continuous for every 10min, sleep tracking on and also notifications on for sedentary and calls and exercise tracking for 30 min a day.Checking SpO2 10 times a day manuallyLifting the watch up to light the screen for nearly 50 times a day.I expected it to last for atleast 5 days+ though(claimed was 7 days). but the step counter sometimes registers steps even if I don't walk :P.Battery life on average 3 days with HR every 10 min on and daily once O2 measurement and sleep tracking.The band is pretty comfortable, no skin irritation or discomfort.This watch is a good budget choice based on my usage.
Overall the product is great, shows msgs and call notifications, measures heart rate, spO2, breathing, workout etc.
